<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-13T12:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-13T12:45:00-05:00" n="753" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d753">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.77/252: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-13T12:00:00-05:45">November 13,
                                1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:55 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>271. I laid your telegram 159, November 12, 3 p.m., before President
                            Moncada last night. He has just told me that he would immediately give
                            Dr. Sacasa cabled instructions in the matter and direct him to say that
                            it was not the intention of the Government of Nicaragua to proceed in an
                            illegal manner when it issued the decree reported upon in my 268,
                            November 9, 1 p.m., nor to terminate its contract with the railway
                            management.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>